description.plain:
From Phoebe’s Facebook:

I was born in Texas
but grew up in Jersey
I have two brothers
and a parakeet
I just moved out to LA
to pursue a dream
do u like love
me too"

Phoebe Ryan was born September 21st, 1990. She began her career as a songwriter and has collaborated with many artists, such as Oh Honey. Her first EP “Mine” released June 9th, 2015. She has received much attention from pop culture advocates such as Billboard and Buzzfeed. In 2015, Phoebe’s hit song “Mine” was featured on MTV’s hit show “Scream”.

songs.title: Mine

description.plain: “Mine” is the first original single from Phoebe Ryan, whose previous career achievements included cowriting Oh Honey’s “Be Okay” and singing on Tritonal’s “Now or Never.” Following its release in January 2015, “Mine” received formidable blog buzz, including features on Earmilk and Billboard. The success of “Mine, ” along with Ryan’s previous mashup of R. Kelly’s “Ignition (Remix)” and Miguel’s “Do You…,” led to a record deal with Columbia Records later in the spring.

songs.title: Dark Side

description.plain:
Dark Side is the first original song of 2017 by LA-based singer-songwriter Phoebe Ryan, her first release since featuring on The Chainsmokers' 2016 hit “All We Know.”

The track was teased by Ryan through Twitter:

https://twitter.com/PhoebeRyan/status/826112149391077377

The song was released through Sony on February 3, 2017.
Entertainment Weekly premiered the song on their website one day before the official release.
